<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1158,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1698,1724]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Comments:</emphasis>
Recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[457,644,1698,1724]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref40746" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2014) Taxonomy of the katydids (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae) from East Asia and adjacent islands. Communication 8. Far Eastern Entomologist, 273, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2014">Gorochov (2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[656,714,1698,1724]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="135 - 157" refId="ref40784" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2016) Systematics of the American katydids (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae). Communication 6. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, 320 (2), 135 - 157. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / trudyzin / 2016.320.2.135" type="journal article" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
) considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Dohrn, 1892" authorityName="Dohrn" authorityYear="1892" box="[857,1162,1698,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Trachyzulpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[857,1009,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Trachyzulpha</emphasis>
Dohrn, 1892
</taxonomicName>
, a genus from Southeast Asia, to be a member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[429,542,1734,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysoniini">Dysoniini</taxonomicName>
, placing it in its own subtribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2014" box="[882,1061,1734,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Trachyzulphina">Trachyzulphina</taxonomicName>
. The supposed justification being the shared lichen mimicry. However, this 
<typeStatus box="[624,672,1771,1797]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
of mimicry has arisen several times in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropterinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phaneropterinae</taxonomicName>
, and also in other katydids like 
<taxonomicName authority="Rentz, Su &amp; Ueshima, 2012" authorityName="Rentz, Su &amp; Ueshima" authorityYear="2012" box="[556,1059,1806,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenagraecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[556,732,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Lichenagraecia</emphasis>
Rentz, Su &amp; Ueshima, 2012
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1128,1231,1806,1832]" name="Australia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[1246,1433,1806,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Conocephalinae">Conocephalinae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rentz, Su &amp; Ueshima" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,364,1842,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Armadillagraeciini">Armadillagraeciini</taxonomicName>
) as well as several groups of the family 
<taxonomicName box="[821,1009,1842,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pseudophyllinae">Pseudophyllinae</taxonomicName>
, and even in Caelifera such as pygmy grasshoppers of the genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Serville, 1838" authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[464,775,1878,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Amorphopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[464,607,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Amorphopus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Serville, J. G. A." box="[616,775,1878,1904]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 776" refId="ref42963" refString="Serville, J. G. A. (1838 [1839]) Histoire naturelle des insectes. Orthopteres, 1839, i - xviii, 1 - 776." type="journal article" year="1838">Serville, 1838</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hancock, 1907" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1907" box="[833,1170,1878,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eomorphopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[833,990,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Eomorphopus</emphasis>
Hancock, 1907
</taxonomicName>
from the Amazon (
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Silva, D. S. M. &amp; Mendes, D. M. D. &amp; Pereira, M. &amp; Domenico, F. &amp; Sperber, C. F." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="45 - 62" refId="ref39767" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., Silva, D. S. M., Mendes, D. M. D., Pereira, M., Domenico, F. &amp; Sperber, C. F. (2019 a) Review of the tribe Amorphopini (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Metrodorinae): pygmy moss-lichen tetrigids from the Amazon rainforest. Journal of Orthoptera Research, 29 (1), 45 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / jor. 29.33717" type="journal article" year="2019">
Cadena-Castañeda 
<emphasis box="[336,385,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 2019a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Mendes, D. M. D. &amp; Silva, D. S. M. &amp; Cardona-Granda, J. M. &amp; Garcia Garcia, A. &amp; Tumbrinck, J." box="[482,558,1914,1940]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref39859" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., Mendes, D. M. D., Silva, D. S. M., Cardona-Granda, J. M., Garcia Garcia, A. &amp; Tumbrinck, J. (2019 b) Systematics and biogeography of the genus Scaria Bolivar, 1887 (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Batrachideinae). Zootaxa, 4675 (1), 1 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4675.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">2019b</bibRefCitation>
). An adaptation to a particular 
<typeStatus box="[904,952,1915,1941]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
of environment or microhabitat is not necessarily associated with a particular taxonomic group. Therefore, the Trachyzulphini 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1108,1189,1950,1976]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1108,1189,1950,1976]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">n. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are here elevated to a separate tribe of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[380,565,1986,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropterinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phaneropterinae</taxonomicName>
, based on the original diagnosis (
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[937,1119,1986,2012]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref40746" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2014) Taxonomy of the katydids (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae) from East Asia and adjacent islands. Communication 8. Far Eastern Entomologist, 273, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2014">Gorochov 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876239" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6876239" box="[151,752,1917,1942]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876239/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" startId="20.[151,250,1917,1941]" targetBox="[151,1436,182,1892]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,752,1917,1942]" box="[151,752,1917,1942]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1917,1941]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">FIGURE 11.</emphasis>
Pictorial key to the genera of tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[645,748,1917,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysoniini">Dysoniini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Moreover, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[323,517,151,177]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="135 - 157" refId="ref40784" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2016) Systematics of the American katydids (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae). Communication 6. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, 320 (2), 135 - 157. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / trudyzin / 2016.320.2.135" type="journal article" year="2016">Gorochov (2016)</bibRefCitation>
proposed to reduce 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García, 2022" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García" authorityYear="2022" box="[746,894,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="trib. n." tribe="Pycnopalpini">Pycnopalpini</taxonomicName>
to a subtribe of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[1079,1192,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysoniini">Dysoniini</taxonomicName>
, arguing that the posteromedial denticle or spine on the upper rostral tubercle is also present in some representatives of that group. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García, 2022" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García" authorityYear="2022" box="[268,416,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="trib. n." tribe="Pycnopalpini">Pycnopalpini</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[447,557,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysoniini">Dysoniini</taxonomicName>
do not belong to a monophyletic group according to the most comprehensive phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mugleston et al. 2018)" baseAuthorityName="Mugleston" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[310,741,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Tettigoniidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Mugleston, J. D. &amp; Naegle, M. &amp; Song, H. &amp; Whiting, M. F." box="[474,733,259,285]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref41921" refString="Mugleston, J. D., Naegle, M., Song, H. &amp; Whiting, M. F. (2018) A comprehensive phylogeny of Tettigoniidae (Orthoptera: Ensifera) reveals extensive ecomorph convergence and widespread taxonomic incongruence. Insect Systematics and Diversity, 2 (4), 1 - 27. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / isd / ixy 010" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mugleston 
<emphasis box="[605,656,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García, 2022" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García" authorityYear="2022" box="[806,954,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="trib. n." tribe="Pycnopalpini">Pycnopalpini</taxonomicName>
are considered a tribe with two subtribes, Pycopalpina and Theiina (
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[443,732,295,321]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="149 - 163" refId="ref38888" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2014 a) La tribu Pycnopalpini trib. n. (Orthoptera, Tettigonioidea, Phaneropteridae): segunda contribucion a la organizacion supragenerica de los faneropterinos neotropicales. Animal Biodiversity and Conservation, 37 (2), 149 - 163." type="journal article" year="2014">Cadena-Castañeda 2014a</bibRefCitation>
, Cigliano 
<emphasis box="[847,903,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2022).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,357]" box="[199,971,331,357]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<figureCitation box="[199,359,331,357]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 11" captionStart-1="FIGURE 12" captionStart-2="FIGURE 13" captionStart-3="FIGURE 14" captionStartId-0="20.[151,250,1917,1941]" captionStartId-1="21.[151,250,1986,2010]" captionStartId-2="22.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionStartId-3="23.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,182,1892]" captionTargetBox-1="[155,1435,381,1962]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,181,1847]" captionTargetBox-3="[151,1425,181,1904]" captionTargetId-0="figure-21@20.[151,1436,181,1893]" captionTargetId-1="figure-110@21.[151,1435,381,1963]" captionTargetId-2="figure-21@22.[151,1436,181,1848]" captionTargetId-3="figure-22@23.[151,1436,181,1905]" captionTargetPageId-0="20" captionTargetPageId-1="21" captionTargetPageId-2="22" captionTargetPageId-3="23" captionText-0="FIGURE 11. Pictorial key to the genera of tribe Dysoniini." captionText-1="FIGURE 12. Pictorial key to the genera of Dysoniini (Markiina n. subtr.)." captionText-2="FIGURE 13. Pictorial key to the genera of Dysoniini (Dysoniina n. subtr.)." captionText-3="FIGURE 14. Pictorial key to the genera of Dysoniini (Dysoniina n. subtr.)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876239" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876241" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876243" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876247" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6876239/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6876241/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6876243/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6876247/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figures 11–14</figureCitation>
present a pictorial key for the identification of genera.
</paragraph>
